author: Amir Mizroch
title: Uber Faces New Threat in London
text:
LONDON—Uber Technologies Inc. faced a fresh threat in Europe after London’s top transportation agency proposed stiff new rules for online car-sharing services—a surprise lane change in a capital that had offered a relatively warm embrace to Uber and its competitors.
Transport for London—which oversees public transportation like the Underground and the capital’s fleet of red double-decker buses and black cabs as well as other licensed cars services—outlined new rules Wednesday that would significantly stiffen requirements...
